id: pm-tyj8
title: "gc --scope checkpoints: prune stale bulk-mutation checkpoint files"
description: "pm gc currently covers scopes: index, embeddings, runtime, locks. The checkpoints/ directory (written by update-many and close-many rollback logic) is never collected. Old checkpoint files accumulate indefinitely under .agents/pm/checkpoints/. There is no TTL or gc coverage for this scope."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[3]: "area:storage",chore,gc
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:02:04.103Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-19T18:27:35.575Z"
author: audit-data-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- Add `checkpoints` to `GC_SCOPE_VALUES` in gc.ts\n- GC sweeps `checkpoints/` by `created_at` age (default: prune files older than N days, configurable)\n- `--dry-run` shows what would be removed\n- Contract/flag tests updated; `pm gc --scope checkpoints` documented\n- At minimum, document the checkpoints directory and advise manual cleanup in the guide"
parent: pm-o2kc
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: "Added pm gc --scope checkpoints: runCheckpointGc sweeps checkpoints/ and prunes rollback checkpoints older than checkpoints.retention_days (default 14, configurable via pm config set checkpoints_retention_days <n>). Unparseable/unreadable checkpoints are retained safety-first (mirrors the locks sweep), dry-run + extension hooks supported, and the result carries a checkpoints summary (scanned/removed/retained/retention_days)."
expected_result: "checkpoints is a first-class gc scope with configurable age-based retention, dry-run, and contract/docs coverage."
actual_result: "Scope wired end-to-end (commander, contracts golden, completion, MCP param table, docs); verified by checkpoint-gc.spec.ts + gc-command.spec.ts + a temp-dir smoke test; 100/100/100/100."
