close_reason: Implemented checkpoints gc scope + checkpoints.retention_days config in feat/gc-storage-durability; full tests/docs/contracts; 100% coverage.
body: "## Context\n\n`src/core/checkpoint/mutation-checkpoint.ts` writes checkpoint JSON files under `checkpoints/<subdir>/`. The `pm gc` command at `src/cli/commands/gc.ts:13` defines `GC_SCOPE_VALUES = ['index', 'embeddings', 'runtime', 'locks']` — checkpoints is absent.\n\nCheckpoint files include `created_at`, `author`, and `items` but have no TTL field. A project running bulk mutations regularly accumulates these files with no way to reclaim them other than manual deletion.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Add `checkpoints` to `GC_SCOPE_VALUES` in gc.ts\n- [ ] GC sweeps `checkpoints/` by `created_at` age (default: prune files older than N days, configurable)\n- [ ] `--dry-run` shows what would be removed\n- [ ] Contract/flag tests updated; `pm gc --scope checkpoints` documented\n- [ ] At minimum, document the checkpoints directory and advise manual cleanup in the guide\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `src/cli/commands/gc.ts:13` — `GC_SCOPE_VALUES` does not include checkpoints\n- `src/core/checkpoint/mutation-checkpoint.ts:78-88` — writes to `checkpoints/<subdir>/`\n- `.agents/pm/checkpoints/update-many/` exists in this repo with accumulated files"
